==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chalcopyrite
<hw>Chal`co*pyr"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chalko`s</grk> brass + E. <ets>pyrite</ets>. So named from its
color.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Copper pyrites, or yellow copper
ore; a common ore of copper, containing copper, iron, and sulphur. It
occurs massive and in tetragonal crystals of a bright brass yellow
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaldaic</ent>⟦br⟧
